INSTALL
=======

1. Install dependencys

Archlinux:
   * rsync
   * boost-libs
   * boost
   * pkg-config
   * libsigc++
   * make
   * gcc
   * mongodb
   * neon


Fedora 17:
  * libsigc++
  * boost-devel
  * gtkmm30-devel
  * inotify-tools-devel
  * rsync
  * gcc-c++
  * make


2. Build dob
   ==> make 

USAGE
=======

1. Create some folder you want use as syncronization folder
   ==> mkdir /home/<Your username>/Backup

2. Edit the configfile, if it not exists just create one
   ==> create: touch dob.conf
   ==> edit  : syncFolder=/home/<Your username>/Backup/
       	       syncType= syncronize 
	       syncProtocol = rsync || git || https
	       destUser= username
	       destHost= server IP
	       destPort= server rsync port or leave empty for standard
       	       destFolder=/<syncronization>/<Folder>/
	       ignore=file (is like regex *file*)
	       sshPort= server ssh port or leave empty for standard

    NOTE: if rsync is used, destUser needs to be the rsync and ssh login. 
	  Consider this, when writing your rsyncd.conf on the destHost.
 

3. Start the programm
   ==> ./dob --config=dob.conf 
	
4. Enjoy the your syncronization deamon without doing anything

TRICKS
=======

* You don't need to copy data into you syncronization folder.
  The easiest way is just creating symlinks into it.
  ==> cd /home/<Your username>/Backup
  ==> ln -s ../<New Folder> .


